{# Admin notification email template (L3-MAIL-015 / L3-MAIL-016).

   Rendered when an outbound email exceeds `mail.max_email_size_bytes`
   (per L3-MAIL-030 step 3). The template SHALL accept ONLY these three
   variables and SHALL NOT interpolate any user-supplied content from
   the failing run — `run_id` is the canonical UUID4 mint per
   `domain.ids.new_run_id` (no template metacharacters), `failure_reason`
   is the literal `"EMAIL_SIZE_EXCEEDED"` enum value (operator-controlled
   string), and `timestamp` is the ISO-8601-Z formatted clock reading.

   Autoescape is enforced by the rendering Environment to neutralize
   any unexpected metacharacter in `run_id` (per L3-MAIL-016). The
   Subject line above body text uses `{{ run_id }}` with the same
   discipline.

   This is a plain-text email (no HTML); operators reading via SMTP
   capture / local mail clients see the same format regardless of
   user-agent.
#}
Message-Service operational alert.

A run could not be delivered because the rendered email exceeded the
configured maximum size.

  Run ID:        {{ run_id }}
  Failure:       {{ failure_reason }}
  Timestamp:     {{ timestamp }}

The rendered report has been persisted and is available through the
dashboard's resend interface for review or manual delivery.

This is an automated notification from the Message Service. No reply
is expected; please consult the service log for the structured
"admin_notification_sent" event keyed by run_id for further detail.
